The '''''Egyptian Center for Economic and Social Rights''''' ('''ECESR''') is an Egyptian [[non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] legal and research organization which addresses issues of [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] and [[Arabs|Arabic]] [[human rights]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About us |url=http://ecesr.org/en/?page_id=5331 |website=ecesr.org |accessdate=24 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402091104/http://ecesr.org/en/?page_id=5331 |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df= }}</ref>
== Outreach == The ECESR sometimes coordinates with other [[non-governmental organizations|NGO]]s to address human rights issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=Egypt|url=http://cesr.org/section.php?id=60|website=Center for Economic and Social Rights|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> In a report titled ''<nowiki>'</nowiki>Above the State<nowiki>'</nowiki>'' the ECESR suggested that increased foreign investment may not lead to improved conditions for most Egyptians.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Hend El-Behary|title=ECESR: Foreign investments don't equal economic development|url=http://www.egyptindependent.com/news/ecesr-foreign-investments-don-t-equal-economic-development|website=Egypt Independent|accessdate=24 April 2015|date=24 February 2015}}</ref>
== Police raids == ECESR offices have been subjected to multiple raids by Egyptian police leading to protest from numerous other agencies.<ref>{{cite web|title=NCHR follows up police raid on ECESR|url=http://www.thecairopost.com/news/59865/news/nchr-police-raid-ecesr|website=The Cairo Post|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=EGYPT: Security Forces Raid The Egyptian Center For Economic And Social Rights, Alexandria Branch, And Sexually Harass Females|url=https://www.fidh.org/International-Federation-for-Human-Rights/north-africa-middle-east/egypt/15374-egypt-security-forces-raid-the-egyptian-center-for-economic-and-social|website=International Federation for Human Rights (FIDH)|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=In solidarity with the "Egyptian Center for Economic and Social Rights" (ECESR)|url=http://www.socialwatch.org/node/16336|website=SOCIAL WATCH|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Egyptian Human Rights Organizations Oppressed… A Return to what is Worse than the Pre-January 25th -Era|url=http://www.cihrs.org/?p=7749&lang=en|website=Cairo Institute for Human Rights Studies|accessdate=24 April 2015|date=December 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Aaron T. Rose|title=ECESR raid raises international ire|url=http://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2013/12/21/ecesr-raid-raises-international-ire/|website=Daily News Egypt|accessdate=24 April 2015|date=December 21, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Egypt: 15 activists released after second police raid on Alexandria NGO|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/articles/news/2014/05/egypt-least-activists-arrested-alexandria-police-raid-ngo-again/|website=Amnesty International|accessdate=24 April 2015|date=22 May 2014}}</ref>
